de.uniheidelberg.cl.swp.mlprocess
Class InstanceContainer

java.lang.Object
  de.uniheidelberg.cl.swp.mlprocess.InstanceContainer

public class InstanceContainer
extends java.lang.Object

A container for WEKA Instances utilized by MLProcess.
This is a temporary container for providing the attribute structure which WEKA requests.

addCorefInstance

public weka.core.Instance addCorefInstance(CoreferencePair corefPair,
                                           java.lang.String acr,
                                           java.lang.String result)
Takes a single CoreferencePair and adds it to the Instances.
This method is used in the training process and + or - will be added.
This is done by matching all the Attributes to the corresponding features of the CoreferencePair.

Parameters:
corefPair - CoreferencePair to be added.
acr - ACR-System.
result - Result of the ACR-System for the CoreferencePair-candidate.
Returns:
Instance object which has been added.

Takes a single CoreferencePair and adds it to the Instances.
This method is used in the test process and "?" will be added automatically.
